<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-05-01T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-05-01T15:00:00-05:00" n="634" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d634">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/3360: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Moore</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-01T16:00:00-04:00">May 1, 1929—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>51. Your 87, April 30, 3 p.m., paragraph two. There must be a mistake
                            regarding this as Ambassador Davila has not called at the Department for
                            over a week, that is not since prior to the time this question came
                            up.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>